  });
});
```

#### 9. Express Exposes `X-Powered-By: Express` Header

This fingerprints your server technology, aiding reconnaissance.

```js
// ✅ Disable the header (helmet also does this)
app.disable('x-powered-by');
```

#### 10. Hardcoded Port with No Environment Configuration

Port `3000` is hardcoded. In production, configuration should come from environment variables, and secrets/config should never be hardcoded.

```js
// ✅ Use environment variable with fallback
const PORT = process.env.PORT || 3000;
app.listen(PORT, () => {
  console.log(`Server running on port ${PORT}`);
});
```

#### 11. No Request Logging / Audit Trail (OWASP A09: Security Logging and Monitoring Failures)

There is no request logging, making incident investigation impossible.

```js
// ✅ Add structured logging
const morgan = require('morgan');
app.use(morgan('combined'));  // Or use winston/pino for structured JSON logs
